    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment is accepted at Medium assurance level. Ten of thirteen V&V 40 factors are fully assessed and meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) is assessed but below the required level, and two factors (Numerical solver error, Model form) are recorded as not-assessed on the basis that detailed evaluation was considered beyond the scope of the current submission cycle. Given that the model risk level is 3 and decision consequence is Medium, the team acknowledges that the not-assessed factors represent a gap in the evidence package; however, the strong quantitative validation results (E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs, errors < 10%) and the multi-laboratory experimental basis are judged sufficient to support an Accepted decision for the non-cannulated pedicle screw COU at this time.",
